    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "thanks. i see what u mean, but honestly when people talk about the \"climate emergency\" and how we need to decarbonize fast, it feels like nuclear is the only one that actually scales up quickly enough compared to solar or wind which can be intermittent. do you think it's realistic to meet climate goals without leaning heavily on nuclear?",
