      "role": "user",
      "content": "i get the construction time issue, but the intermittency of renewables seems like an even bigger bottleneck if we want a stable grid. if we don't have a baseload like nuclear to back them up, aren't we basically just setting ourselves up for failure? it feels like dismissing nuclear because of the timeline is kind of ignoring the actual physics of the power grid.",
